ExecDesc.value: Microsoft DirectX SAMI File Parsing Code Execution (IPv6 Version)

EngDesc.value: A buffer overflow vulnerability exists in Microsoft DirectX application framework. The vulnerability is due to the way certain DirectX libraries handle specially crafted Synchronized Accessible Media Interchange (SAMI) file type. A remote attacker could exploit this vulnerability by persuading a user to open a specially crafted SAMI file, potentially causing arbitrary code to be injected and executed in the security context of the logged in user. (IPv6 Version)
